  startRecieving: 1
  printToConsole: 0
  data: 
  UDP_Hands_notes: 'This script will receive data from a python script that is sending
    data over UDP. The data will be received on the port that is set in the port
    variable. The data will be stored in the data variable. The data can be printed
    to the console by setting the printToConsole variable to true. The startRecieving
    variable can be set to false to stop receiving data. The data can be accessed
    by other scripts by using the data variable '
  note: The default camera can only be changed in the python hand tracking script.
